# isLike(_:)

**Instance Method**

Returns a Boolean value that indicates whether the receiver is “like” another given object.

## Declaration

```swift
func isLike(_ object: String) -> Bool
```

## Parameters

- **object**: The object with which to compare the receiver.

## Return Value

[doc://com.apple.objectivec/documentation/ObjectiveC/YES] if the receiver is considered to be “like” `object`, otherwise [doc://com.apple.objectivec/documentation/ObjectiveC/NO].

## Discussion

Currently, [doc://com.apple.objectivec/documentation/ObjectiveC/NSObject-swift.class/isLike(_:)] messages are never sent to any object from within Cocoa itself.

The default implementation for this method provided by `NSObject` method returns [doc://com.apple.objectivec/documentation/ObjectiveC/NO]. `NSString` also provides an implementation of this method, which returns [doc://com.apple.objectivec/documentation/ObjectiveC/YES] if the receiver matches a pattern described by `object`.
